SIMPLE: unwell
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unwell
<hw>Un*well"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not well;
indisposed; not in good health; somewhat ill; ailing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Specifically, ill from
menstruation; affected with, or having, catamenial;
menstruant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This word was formerly regarded as an Americanism, but
is now in common use among all who speak the English
language.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unwellness</ent>⟦br⟧
